.TH eroosterctl-user-list 1 "June 2026" "eroosterctl" "Erooster Manual"
.SH NAME
eroosterctl\-user\-list \- list all mail users
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eroosterctl user list
[\fI\-\-output\fR \fBtable\fR|\fBjson\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Retrieves all registered mail users from the database and prints them in the
requested format. The list is sorted alphabetically.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fBtable\fR|\fBjson\fR
\fBtable\fR (default) renders a single \fBUSERNAME\fR column.
\fBjson\fR emits a JSON array of objects with a \fIusername\fR field.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
# Table output
eroosterctl user list

# Ansible\-friendly JSON
eroosterctl --output json user list

# Count users in a script
eroosterctl --output json user list | jq length
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBeroosterctl\-user\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-user\-add\fR(1),
\fBeroosterctl\-user\-delete\fR(1)
